articles.title: Adams Meets Trump: Bridging New York's Partisan Divide
articles.description: New York Mayor Eric Adams met with President-elect Donald Trump in Florida to discuss federal support for the city's infrastructure and economy. Despite legal charges against Adams, their discussion focused on bipartisan collaboration, excluding the mayor's corruption case.
articles.content:
